itunes:summary:
Ross Patterson, Jarred Taylor, and Dan Hollaway welcome one of our favorites, Tyley Cornack from Tiny Cinema on the show.  He just finished starring, writing, and directing his controversial movie "Buttboy" based on the the viral sketch of the same name, in which a whole world exists inside of a man's ass.  We also chat about what it's like to "track" a person at random for the day, and Tyler tells us about the time an ex-girlfriend smashed a full guitar over his head.
